timeline.bodyText:
These tests could be rewritten easily so that each test passes its own Servlet implementation to the Server startup.
Then, it would be easy to use a latch to coordinate with the client, so that the test does not need to wait 2000 ms but it will be immediate.
Pseudo code:
@Test
public void test() {
  CountDownLatch latch = new CountDownLatch(1);
  start(new HttpServlet() {
    service(request, response) {
      response.flushBuffer();
      latch.await();
    }
  });

  client.newRequest(...)
    .onResponseHeaders(response -> latch.countDown())
    ...
    .send();
}

